Package: spice-resize-monitor
Version: 1.0.0-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Sascha Ittner <sascha.ittner@modusoft.de>
Installed-Size: 18
Depends: x11-utils, x11-xserver-utils, spice-vdagent
Section: x11
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/sittner/spice-resize-monitor
Description: SPICE auto-resize monitor for non-GNOME desktops
 spice-vdagent fails to auto-apply display resolution changes on
 desktops that don't provide org.gnome.Mutter.DisplayConfig over DBus
 (e.g. MATE, XFCE, LXQt, etc.).
 .
 This package provides a simple event-driven monitor that listens for
 X RandR events and applies the SPICE-provided preferred resolution
 automatically.
